               <msContents>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_24-item1">
                     <title key="work_14583">Sermons</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                     <note>A collection of sermons, incomplete at the beginning and end. The first sermon, which is preceded by an incomplete preface, is apparently by <persName key="person_52084579" role="aut">John Russell</persName>, a Franciscan, preaching the crusade of 1291</note>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_24-item1-item1">
                        <locus>(fol.2v)</locus>
                        <rubric>Memorialia de sacra cruce que viris literatis poterunt predicari</rubric>
                        <incipit>Michi absit gloriari …Antequam loquar de cruce crucifixi</incipit>
                        <note>(there is a gap after fol.2v)</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_24-item1-item2">
                        <locus>(fol.10v)</locus>
                        <rubric>Collatio ad milites</rubric>
                        <incipit>Labora sicut bonus miles... Hec sunt verba beati Pauli</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_24-item1-item3">
                        <locus>(fol.16)</locus>
                        <rubric>Collatio in visitatione facienda communiter</rubric>
                        <incipit>Fratres tuos visitabis… Unum verbum communiter dicitur et est verum, ‘velit nolit vadit sacerdos ad synodum’</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_24-item1-item4">
                        <locus>(fol.19v)</locus>
                        <rubric>
                           <sic>Colacio</sic> in visitacione facienda inter religiosos</rubric>
                        <incipit>Descendi in ortum meum…Fratres scire debetis quod prelatus</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_24-item1-item5">
                        <locus>(fol.23v)</locus>
                        <rubric>Materia collationis in ordinibus faciendis</rubric>
                        <incipit>Ego sternam per ordinem…Hoc verbum scribitur in prophetia Ysaye</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_24-item1-item6">
                        <locus>(fol.30r)</locus>
                        <rubric>De virginibus consecrandis collatio</rubric>
                        <incipit>Despondi vos uni viro…Istud verbum beati Pauli scribitur</incipit>
                        <note>A quire is lost after fol.31 and the end of this and the beginning of the next sermon is lost</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_24-item1-item7">
                        <locus>(fol.33v)</locus>
                        <rubric>Collatio de tribus virtutibus theologicis </rubric>
                        <incipit>Nunc manent fides, spes caritas…Ista sunt verba beati Paul</incipit>
                        <note>There is a gap in the text after fol. 39v due to the loss of a quire.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_th_e_24-item1-item8">
                        <locus>(fol.41v)</locus>
                        <rubric>Collacio de peccatis mortalibs</rubric>
                        <incipit>Cave ne aliquando consencias. Istud verbum scribitur. Thob. c.4o.</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <note>See B.L.R. II (1947) 169.</note>
                  </msItem>
